<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1441,673,730]" lastBlockId="27.[192,1440,194,250]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,349,673,697]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">Discussion.</emphasis>
The lack of long white setae laterally on the pronotum and presence of elongate white bristles on the forecoxa distinguishes this species in the group. Also, the short hindtibial spurs which do not reach apex of tarsomere II is an important discriminating character. The male genitalia are diagnostic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
